reviews.review: Much better than what Rotten Tomatoes says and better than Last Jedi. Good ending to the series
it was entertaining and captured some of the spirit of the original Star Wars. but first hour was too long and did not add to enjoyment

STAR WARS: RISE OF SKYWALKER was spectacular, a rousing conclusion to a favorite Space Opera series. Unlike its predecessor, every borderline decision made here fell toward things I enjoy and I thought this was a busy but entertaining wrap-up. I'm ready for the Skywalker saga to be complete and am looking forward to something new (Kyle Katarn, anyone?).

Phew!  OK, the first 40 minutes are a bit chaotic and it does get a bit 'friendship forever' in places but thank the Jedi JJ pulled it all together and gave me an epic ending to the saga that started when I was 11 years old. A great Star Wars film. Rise Skywalker!

All the critics are saying that Rise of Skywalker is for fanboys, that it's terrible because it undos Johnson TLJ.Well, good. I want nostalgia. If, you are a true Star Wars fan & read comics & expanded than this story & a certain person coming back to life is not new. Go watch it...screw the critics.
While the movie moves through things fast it does the job of keeping you entertained and tying up the saga. It by no means deserves such disgust from the community.

42 years, 11 films, countless memories, & unforgettable characters. With a soundtrack for the ages, a saga concludes, yet the legends rise never to be forgotten, and Hope springs eternal! #StoryToldWell #MayTheForceBeWithYou

Like all Star Wars films that came before, The Rise of Skywalker has its issues but it does a great job of wrapping up the saga as we know it. Sparking debates for years to come, TROS stands as the best movie in the sequels trilogy. Go see it with an open mind and don't listen to the critics.
